4.  Rural Pension Internal Control Specialist (7 person-months)  
7.  The  consultant  will  assume  overall  responsibility  for  designing  the  internal  control 
mechanism  for  the  rural  pension  system  in  the  PRC.  The  consultant  must  have  a  good 
command of social security and governance theory. He or she must also have experience with 
the internal control practices. Specifically, the consultant will 
(i)  evaluate the capabilities of the existing monitoring systems at the central and 
local  government  levels  and  their  adequacy  to  monitor  and  supervise  rural 
pension system implementation; 
(ii)  develop guidelines for standardizing the internal control system; 
(iii)  assist in the drafting of the report, thematic reports, and draft policy document;  
(iv)  prepare policy notes and technical notes for relevant issues; and  
(v)  deliver sessions during training workshops on internal control issues.
